    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>It Is Deadly Serious</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Herman Gross letter on Yankees pitcher Roger Clemons hitting Mets catcher Mike Piazza with pitch recalls fatal accident in 1920's when Carl Mays beaned and killed Ray Chapman$</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I imagine there are very few fans alive who can remember (as I do) the fatal accident in the early 1920's when the sidewinder pitcher Carl Mays beaned and killed Ray Chapman. Without a helmet, that could have happened to Piazza. The sound of the crack on the helmet was as loud as the crack of a bat on a ball.</p>
        <p>HERMAN GROSS  Great Neck, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
